org.openehealth.ipf.commons.flow.jmx

Class FlowPurgerMBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openehealth.ipf.commons.flow.jmx.FlowPurgerMBean
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DisposableBean, InitializingBean

    @ManagedResource(objectName="org.openehealth.ipf:type=service,name=FlowPurger",
                 description="Flow purge service")
public class FlowPurgerMBean
extends Object
implements InitializingBean, DisposableBean
    MBean for managing application-specific purge operations for out-dated flows. Out-dated flows are removed from the database either manually or periodically based on cron expressions.
    Author:
    Martin Krasser
